      <item>
        <title>Otr plugin  for  gajim</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[Patrick]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>gajim OTR is discouraged.</p>
<p><a href="https://dev.gajim.org/gajim/gajim-plugins/wikis/OffTheRecordPlugin" rel="nofollow noopener">https://dev.gajim.org/gajim/gajim-plugins/wikis/OffTheRecordPlugin</a> says</p>
<blockquote>
<ul>
<li>There are some bugs that can lead to accidently sending plaintext. It is recommended to use PGP or OMEMO instead. See <a href="http://forums.whonix.org/gajim/gajim-plugins/wikis/OmemoGajimPlugin">OMEMO</a>.</li>
<li>The plugin won’t work with Gajim &gt;= 1.0 as it was not ported to python3. There is no port planned.</li>
</ul>
</blockquote>
<p>What about using OMEMO instead?</p>
<p><a href="https://www.whonix.org/wiki/Chat#Gajim" rel="nofollow noopener">https://www.whonix.org/wiki/Chat#Gajim</a> says</p>
<blockquote>
<p>sudo apt-get update</p>
</blockquote>
<blockquote>
<p>sudo apt-get install gajim gajim-omemo gajim-httpupload</p>
</blockquote>
          <p><a href="http://forums.whonix.org/t/otr-plugin-for-gajim/8241/2">Read full topic</a></p>
        ]]></description>
